generates unique identifiers

Source: R/dev-utils.R
uuid_generate.Rd

generates unique identifiers based on uuid::UUIDgenerate().

Usage

uuid_generate(n = 1, ...)

Arguments

n

integer, number of unique identifiers to generate.

...

arguments sent to uuid::UUIDgenerate()

Examples

uuid_generate(n = 5)
#> [1] "894f8f98-85ee-4ed5-8333-aadbbed8c59b"
#> [2] "e5871890-d915-4286-a8a8-04e98c6424ae"
#> [3] "60a7124f-e480-492b-9679-88c10b66b69d"
#> [4] "7aea0310-c9b1-4a42-9fb4-bc7886caaa4a"
#> [5] "a6ab130d-d1d9-4e05-9f5e-76b721656195"
